      "rationale": "Three-level mesh convergence study performed on the pedicle screw-rod construct geometry. Richardson extrapolation yields discretization error estimate of 0.8% on stiffness QoI. Final mesh (1.2M elements, C3D8I formulation) selected as production mesh. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver residual convergence criteria documented; energy balance checks performed for each simulation run.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear solver (Newton-Raphson) convergence confirmed at each load increment; force and moment residuals below 1e-4. Energy balance error <0.05% across all 11 simulation replicates. Solver settings frozen and documented in simulation plan."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation plan reviewed by independent analyst; boundary condition and loading definitions cross-checked against ASTM F1717 test standard.",
      "rationale": "Simulation plan formally reviewed by two independent senior analysts not involved in model construction. Boundary conditions (fixed inferior fixture, load applied at superior fixture offset 75 mm) verified against ASTM F1717-15 Section 8. No use errors identified."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Constitutive model selection justified for Ti-6Al-4V at quasi-static loading rates; contact formulation appropriate for screw-rod interface behavior.",
      "rationale": "Isotropic linear-elastic model with bilinear plasticity (E=114 GPa, σ_y=880 MPa, tangent modulus=1.2 GPa) applied to Ti-6Al-4V per published material characterization data. Contact formulation uses augmented Lagrangian with friction coefficient μ=0.2, consistent with literature for titanium-titanium interfaces. Model form uncertainty assessed as low for quasi-static loading."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from traceable coupon test data; geometric inputs derived from CMM measurements of production components.",
      "rationale": "Material properties (E, σ_y, tangent modulus) sourced from lot-specific coupon tensile testing (n=5 per lot, two lots). Geometric inputs derived from CMM measurements of 5 production screws and rods; nominal dimensions used with dimensional variability characterized. Input uncertainty propagated through sensitivity analysis."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test specimens traceable to production lots; dimensional inspection completed on a representative sample prior to testing.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs assembled from production-representative components. Dimensional inspection (CMM) performed on 100% of screws and rods prior to assembly. Specimens drawn from two separate production lots to capture inter-lot variability. Traceability records maintained."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of clinically relevant loading rates and environmental conditions (ambient and simulated physiological saline).",
      "rationale": "Testing conducted at a single quasi-static loading rate (5 mm/min) under ambient laboratory conditions only. Simulated physiological saline environment and alternative loading rates not evaluated. This factor is below the required level 3; acknowledged as a limitation in the decision record. The shortfall is accepted given the primary use of the model for regulatory submission comparison to ASTM F1717 standard conditions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation inputs (geometry, material properties, boundary conditions) demonstrably equivalent to test specimen and test setup parameters.",
      "rationale": "FEA geometry derived from CMM data of actual tested specimens. Material properties assigned from same lot as tested components. Fixture geometry and offset distance (75 mm) replicated from test setup drawings. Equivalency confirmed by independent review."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (percent difference and E/uval) applied to all three QoIs; acceptance bounds pre-specified in validation plan.",
      "rationale": "All three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) compared using percent difference and E/uval ratio per ASME V&V 20. Acceptance bounds (<10% difference, E/uval < 1.96) pre-specified in the validation plan prior to data unblinding. All three QoIs pass acceptance criteria."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly correspond to the clinical and regulatory quantities needed to support the intended use decision.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in ASTM F1717 and directly referenced in FDA guidance for spinal implant submissions. These QoIs are mechanistically linked to fatigue life and clinical failure modes (rod fracture, screw pullout). Relevance is high."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities use the same model, same geometry family, and same loading mode as the intended COU application.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on the exact non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw geometry and loading configuration (ASTM F1717 compression-bending) that constitutes the COU. No geometric or loading mode extrapolation required. Validation directly supports the intended regulatory submission use."
